page_0: "That bastard thinks he can just throw me in here and forget about me like that idiot Old Jacob. Poor fool didn't even realise anything was wrong when we bricked his sorry soul in here. Well I'm cleverer than that. I'll figure out this flow locking mechanism, and then I'll get out of here and cut Sturmdrang's foolish throat! Half a share. After all I did for him! It's not greedy, I deserve some damn recognition!"

page_1: "I've got to the water control room at the top, but it seems I have to work the levers at intervals down the shafts to control the water flow, according to the diagrams at the top. Easier said than done with the damn slippery steps - not gonna get my revenge if I slip and break my neck now."
